reviews_data.review_text: This place rocks! You can tell this place is a local favorite with how packed it is on most week nights. Between their board games, dice, books, paint, and miscellaneous nerd stuff, this store is perfect for newbies and collectors alike. My husband and I came here a random Wednesday night to try DND and we still play a few years later! The staff is always super nice and helpful and very cheerful on the phone. We love their consignment board game selection and their board game rentals. You can try a board game for a few bucks for the week and then you get that money back if you buy the game! This has led to us buying a few too many board games!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the great review, Camille! We love helping people get into the hobby and find games they love. We are very glad to hear you have enjoyed your time at the store!

reviews_data.review_text: Best Place for MTG cards. Huge fan. One of the better places to learn new games for those just starting out. The staff here is incredibly helpful and go out of their way to help all their customers.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you! We love to help people learn new games.

reviews_data.review_text:
Stopped in to look for some fun dice, board game accessories, and games. We left with a stack of new board games (whoops) and a set of dice with little piggies with top hats and bow ties - we have a pet pig so it seemed fitting. Didn't find quite what I was looking for other accessories but tbf I'm not sure what I was looking for anyway.

We were greeted when we walked in and the employee even offered to make recommendations even though he was in the middle of teaching a group how to play something. Pretty friendly and there seemed to be lots of room for events etc.

The rewards program seems very generous - $5 store credit for every $100 spent basically. Love that you can rent games!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the great review, Dani! We love helping new customers as well as our regulars, and our rewards program helps us do that. I'm glad you had a good time at the store, and we'd love to see you back in sometime soon!

reviews_data.review_text: This is such a gem for the niche that is the tabletop. I prefer coming here to ordering online for all my board game needs. Not because it is cheaper, the prices are fair, but because of what they are trying to do for the community. Everyday of the week almost has an event, from miniture painting, to Magic the Gathering night, to D&D adventure clubs. I go out of my way to support this business on their quest to serve the community. The staff is friendly and knowledgeable, and never short of a recommendation for a game. They have board games for rent so you can try before you buy. All in all, a solid 5 stars of gold.

reviews_data.review_text:
Your local game store is a great small business in the community for board games and TTRPGs (TableTop Roleplay Games). The owners and employees are all quite kind, and I've known them for years. If you're looking into MtG (Magic: the Gathering) or D&D (Dungeons and dragons), the store is a great place to go.

I was really blessed with having them be so close to home, and I've had a wonderful experience through the years with them.

Some quick questions you may have:

They do not sell comic books, and they have a very limited consignment selection of single mtg cards. They also do not sell video games.

reviews_data.review_text: We have occasionally dropped into this store over the years to check out the different games and equipment they have. Recently we had a special request from a family member for a Japanese shogi board for a birthday gift. At the time it was extremely difficult to get them personally imported in and theyre very rare to find in stock in the states. We tried calling several other tabletop stores in the area. The guys here were polite, understanding, and extremely helpful. They were able to special order the board AND receive well before the birthday deadline. The board is in excellent shape and perfect to give as a gift. Communication was excellent as well! As a bonus we also found a board game while we were shopping around at the time. It was super fun too! Looking forward to shopping here again in the future and possibly playing some games there as well! Thank you so much for making this birthday gift so special!

reviews_data.review_text: Great store or greatest store?

Your Local Game Store (YLGS) is a family oriented and friendly place. Atypical for the genre, YLGS is full of light due to the windows on both ends.

There is a wide selection of board games and the more popular role playing games. Their selection of miniature games is small but the major players are represented.

The main highlight is the gaming area. In a space as cozy as YLGS there is a substantial gaming area. All areas of gaming, from RPGs to full miniature battles can easily be supported. Miniature wargame tournaments (40k or fantasy) would be difficult to pull off at standard point values.

All in all YLGS is a beacon of light in what has been for several years an abyss. In order for the beacon to grow, it must be fed and nurtured.

In the months since YLGS opened, I've found an extended family in both the owners and regulars.  The owners are some of the kindest people that you will ever meet.  While they are extremely knowledgeable about different games - from board games to war games to card games to RPGs, if they don't have an answer, they'll research it and get back to you with incredible speed.  The gaming community is great, and the gaming spaces in the store are plentiful and well-kept.

I frequent this business every Wednesday for their weekly Magic: The Gathering booster draft (starting at 7pm). The owners are friendly and the store is clean/organized. When you're there you're treated like you're family. Besides drafting on Wednesday they have things going on every day of the week (except Sunday when they are closed). It's a fun and friendly environment that is suitable for all ages, any day of the week you walk in there you'll be able to meet some new friends and try out a new game. Also they have worked out a deal with a local pizzeria to get food delivered with no delivery charge, so that's a plus.

You should absolutely check them out whenever you have some free time.

Your local game store is absolutely amazing! Rebecca and Timothy are awesome at what they do and they are extremely nice. They have tons of games and some I personally have never even heard from. They are willing to teach you any game no matter if its card, board or RPG. Visit your local game store I promise you that you will not be disappointed.

I remember you - I think you had a book and a couple of paint brushes in hand when I asked for you to wait a moment so I could help with the other transaction. When I got back to the register, I realized my employee, who was technically not scheduled to work at that time, had helped a regular patron who specifically asked him for something.

When I asked if he'd helped you, he said that he'd not realized someone hadn't been helped. I got so worried because if had been me in your shoes, it would've felt like no one was paying any attention or care to my purchase and needs. I went over to the hobby and miniatures area and then around the tables to find you and apologize, but you were gone. I've felt awful that this happened to you at our store. Sometimes it's busy and we don't get a chance to greet everyone, but we try to make sure that everyone gets our full attention at some point during their time at our establishment. It was my fault, and I apologize profusely.

reviews_data.review_text: Awesome place

Came in for first time to play some L5R. Owner and staff were really friendly and helped teach me the game. Lots of nice open space, snack counter, and clean bathroom. Even though I have to drive by other stores to get there. This will be my new home gaming store.
Great store, excellent selection in stock and friendly staff. More of a 40k player we have no problem getting a table on Thursday and having fun.

This place is great.  I picked up some Hordes stuff late last summer and was interested in trying it out.  I scoped this place out a few times while constructing my army and finally went for miniatures night on Thursday one week in November or December.  Everyone has been extremely welcoming and patient as I learned the ropes and I've made a couple dozen new friends.  I have been in the store most days of the week and it seems there is always something going on and the Warmachine/Hordes scene is particularly excellent.

In general it is unlike some other game stores I have been in as most of the place is open to make room for all the tables.  It's a good size and the  full wall windows on both sides help differentiate it from the usual dungeon-like game store.

Highly recommended.

Excellent location in downtown Matthews. The staff is very helpful and friendly. They carry a wide variety of stock so good chance they have what you are looking for. Great tables for miniature war gaming.

Fourth visit and second attempt to get a game of Hordes going.  No dice.  The location is too small and there are few proper-sized tables. The store is also stuffy and smells a little moldy which could be overlooked if not for the small size and unwelcoming atmosphere.  Locals may like it, but pass on it if you live more than ten minutes from it.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
I'm sorry to hear that you weren't able to find any games. We almost always have Warmachine/Hordes games being played on one of our six full sized (4' x 8') tables. Thursday nights are specifically our miniature nights, and we usually have between 4 and 8 games going on throughout the day.

I'm also sorry to hear that it seemed stuffy or smelly. We try to keep the store as clean and odorless as possible, but when you have over 20-30 people in the store at one time, it can get a little stifled.

We would love to see you in some Thursday to meet the rest of our thriving Warmachine/Hordes community!

reviews_data.review_text: Great store or greatest store?

Your Local Game Store (YLGS) is a family oriented and friendly place. Atypical for the genre, YLGS is full of light due to the windows on both ends.

There is a wide selection of board games and the more popular role playing games. Their selection of miniature games is small but the major players are represented.

The main highlight is the gaming area. In a space as cozy as YLGS there is a substantial gaming area. All areas of gaming, from RPGs to full miniature battles can easily be supported. Miniature wargame tournaments (40k or fantasy) would be difficult to pull off at standard point values.

All in all YLGS is a beacon of light in what has been for several years an abyss. In order for the beacon to grow, it must be fed and nurtured.

In the months since YLGS opened, I've found an extended family in both the owners and regulars.  The owners are some of the kindest people that you will ever meet.  While they are extremely knowledgeable about different games - from board games to war games to card games to RPGs, if they don't have an answer, they'll research it and get back to you with incredible speed.  The gaming community is great, and the gaming spaces in the store are plentiful and well-kept.

I frequent this business every Wednesday for their weekly Magic: The Gathering booster draft (starting at 7pm). The owners are friendly and the store is clean/organized. When you're there you're treated like you're family. Besides drafting on Wednesday they have things going on every day of the week (except Sunday when they are closed). It's a fun and friendly environment that is suitable for all ages, any day of the week you walk in there you'll be able to meet some new friends and try out a new game. Also they have worked out a deal with a local pizzeria to get food delivered with no delivery charge, so that's a plus.

You should absolutely check them out whenever you have some free time.

Your local game store is absolutely amazing! Rebecca and Timothy are awesome at what they do and they are extremely nice. They have tons of games and some I personally have never even heard from. They are willing to teach you any game no matter if its card, board or RPG. Visit your local game store I promise you that you will not be disappointed.
The first time I went there was excellent, they told us about the store, and we got to play a very fun game. I have been there over 10 times and its always fun
